  "birth_place": "Athens",
  "description": "古希臘哲學家",
  "bio": "柏拉圖（古希臘語：Πλάτων，前429年—前347年），古希臘哲學家，雅典人，其著作大多以對話錄形式紀錄，並創辦了著名的柏拉圖學院。柏拉圖是蘇格拉底的學生，亞里斯多德的老師，他們三人被普遍認為是西方哲學的奠基人，史稱「西方三聖」或「希臘三哲」。",
  "bio_source": "zhwiki",
  "description_en": "4th-century BCE Greek philosopher",
  "bio_en": "Plato ( PLAY-toh; Ancient Greek: Πλάτων, Plátōn; born c. 428–423 BC, died 348/347 BC) was an ancient Greek philosopher of Classical Athens who is most commonly considered the foundational thinker of the Western philosophical tradition. An innovator of the literary dialogue and dialectic forms, Plato influenced all the major areas of theoretical philosophy and practical philosophy, and was the founder of the Academy, a philosophical school in Athens where Plato taught the collection of philosophical theories that would later become known as Platonism. \nPlato's most famous contribution is his Theory of Forms (or Ideas), which aims to solve what is now known as the problem of universals.",
  "bio_en_source": "enwiki"
}